Context: The George Brown College has transfer agreements and opportunities for students who wish to transfer to other post-secondary institutions. Students can visit ontransfer.ca for more resources and information. Interested individuals can contact the institution they wish to transfer to for admission requirements, time to complete, and number of transfer credits granted. The text also mentions that students can request course outlines and official transcripts, as well as sign up for updates about application deadlines, college news, events, tours, and more. Contact information provided includes a phone number (416-415-2000), TTY number (1-877-515-5559), and email address (ask.george@georgebrown.ca). The text states that the information on the website is subject to change without notice and should not be viewed as a representation or warranty. Students are responsible for verifying George Brown College fee requirements.
